Package org.zaproxy.zap.extension.httpsessions

Class Summary
ExtensionHttpSessions The HttpSessions Extension handles the existing http sessions on the existing site.
HttpSession The Class HttpSession defines the data that is stored regarding an existing HTTP session on a particular site.
HttpSessionsPanel The HttpSessionsPanel used as a display panel for the ExtensionHttpSessions, allowing the user to view and control the http sessions.
HttpSessionsParam The HttpSessionsParam is used to store the parameters (options) for the ExtensionHttpSessions and related classes.
HttpSessionsSite The Class SiteHttpSessions stores all the information regarding the sessions for a particular Site.
HttpSessionsTableModel The Class HttpSessionsTableModel that is used as a TableModel for the Http Sessions Panel.
OptionsHttpSessionsPanel The OptionsHttpSessionsPanel is used to display and allow the users to modify the settings regarding the behaviour of ExtensionHttpSessions.
OptionsHttpSessionsTableModel The OptionsHttpSessionsTableModel is used as a table model to display the token names for OptionsHttpSessionsPanel.
PopupMenuRemoveSession The PopupMenuRemoveSession is used to delete a http session from the ExtensionHttpSessions .
PopupMenuSetActiveSession The PopupMenuSetActiveSession is used to set the active http session for the ExtensionHttpSessions.
PopupMenuUnsetActiveSession The PopupMenuUnsetActiveSession is used to unset the active http session for the ExtensionHttpSessions.
